author: Karl Friedhoff
title: South Korea’s Emerging Role in Asia
text:
When South Korea’s President Park Geun-hye meets with President Obama in Washington Friday, it will be a meeting without an obvious objective. With the strength of the U.S.-Korea alliance at historic highs, the discussion will instead focus on other problems in the region. North Korea will certainly be a primary topic, as will the need to improve South Korea-Japan relations. But it is South Korea’s ties with China that should top Ms. Park’s agenda.
